			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Margot Landwirt regarding her deportation in August 1944 from the Płaszów concentration camp to Auschwitz, the harsh
					living conditions in the camp, and selections. Landwirt was sent with a transport first to Bergen-Belsen and then to Aschersleben.
					She was liberated by US forces during the death march towards Dachau.</p>
			</abstract>
